                <h1>Understanding the French Revolution: A Brief Overview</h1>
                <p>The French Revolution (1789-1799) was a pivotal period in history marked by the overthrow of the monarchy, the rise of radical political factions, and the establishment of a republic. Driven by Enlightenment ideals, the revolution led to significant social and political change, inspiring movements worldwide in the pursuit of liberty and equality.</p>
